"No," Javlyn called back, "Though there is a friendly creature here. Please leave it alone, it just wants the mushrooms."

The three exchanged a look before coming over and having Javlyn recount the fairly short encounter. Once it was done, they sat to debating.

Javlyn listened curiously as they discussed magical workings gone wrong and things beyond her understanding until finally, she interrupted. "It looks like rain and I do need to be getting home. Do I have your word you will leave the creature alone?"

"Aye, you've got our word," the sole female of the group said. "Actually, would you mind us joining you. I've got a couple questions for you."

Javlyn assented and they started walking. It was engaging conversing with the travelers, enough Javlyn didn't mind it when it started raining shortly after they got moving and then didn't let up the rest of the walk. It definitely wasn't what she expected when she set out, but she felt discovering the truth made it more than worth it.
